# GitHub Project Update Rules

## Text Conversion and Encoding
- Convert all Simplified Chinese characters to Traditional Chinese
- Fix any encoding issues (UTF-8 encoding required)
- Ensure proper display of Chinese characters

## Package Management and Dependencies
- Update all outdated packages to stable versions
- Check for package dependency conflicts
- Remove unused packages
- Ensure package version compatibility
- Update dependency files (composer.json/package.json/requirements.txt)
- Document major version changes and updates

## Documentation Management
- Maintain up-to-date README.md file
- Create README.md if not exists with standard sections:
  - Project description
  - Installation instructions
  - Usage guide
  - Configuration details
  - Dependencies list
  - Contributing guidelines
  - License information
- Keep changelog in README.md or CHANGELOG.md
- Document all version updates with:
  - Version number
  - Release date
  - Changes made
  - Breaking changes
  - New features
  - Bug fixes
- Sync documentation with code changes
- Maintain multilingual documentation if needed

## Code Quality and Documentation
- Add Traditional Chinese comments to explain code functionality
- Fix code syntax errors and bugs
- Implement best practices for code structure
- Maintain consistent code style and indentation

## Code Formatting
- Proper indentation (2 spaces for most languages)
- Consistent line breaks
- Remove trailing whitespace
- Organize imports and dependencies

## File Organization
- Ensure proper file structure
- Maintain clear file naming conventions
- Update documentation files (README, etc.)

## Specific Tasks
1. Convert Simplified Chinese to Traditional Chinese
2. Fix encoding issues and ensure correct text display
3. Check and fix code errors
4. Add Traditional Chinese comments for code documentation
5. Optimize code formatting and structure
6. Update outdated packages and ensure compatibility
7. Update or create README.md with changes
8. Document version updates in changelog

## Implementation Notes
- Use UTF-8 encoding for all files
- Follow language-specific style guides
- Document all major changes
- Maintain version control history
- Regular package update checks
- Set up package update testing environment
- Follow semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)
- Keep documentation synchronized with code changes
